Observations:

An important observation noted while completing this project was that the hand-calculated truth table matched up with the waveform from the software. That means that the function F can be represented in multiple ways for different purposes. It can be represented as a function, as a sum of products, as a truth table, as a waveform, and as a schematic/circuit drawing.

<img width="427" alt="screen shot 2019-02-06 at 8 15 03 pm" src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/33227826/52386521-0e75e800-2a4c-11e9-9f84-aa84682b0d14.png">


I learned how to use the Xilinx ISE design software to create complex circuit schematics, and how to test those schematics for accuracy and efficiency. We learned how to interpret an output waveform, and how to write a sample test bench for a four-input circuit using VHDL. 
